defs.docs: Extra components for use with Mio.

defs.name: channel
defs.docs: Thread safe communication channel implementing `Evented`

defs.name: channel
defs.docs:
Creates a new asynchronous channel, where the `Receiver` can be registered
 with `Poll`.

defs.name: sync_channel
defs.docs:
Creates a new synchronous, bounded channel where the `Receiver` can be
 registered with `Poll`.

defs.name: Sender
defs.docs: The sending half of a channel.

defs.name: SyncSender
defs.docs: The sending half of a synchronous channel.

defs.name: Receiver
defs.docs: The receiving half of a channel.

defs.name: Io
defs.docs: An IO error.

defs.name: Disconnected
defs.docs: The receiving half of the channel has disconnected.

defs.name: SendError
defs.docs: An error returned from the `Sender::send` or `SyncSender::send` function.

defs.name: Io
defs.docs: An IO error.

defs.name: Full
defs.docs: Data could not be sent because it would require the callee to block.

defs.name: Disconnected
defs.docs: The receiving half of the channel has disconnected.

defs.name: TrySendError
defs.docs: An error returned from the `SyncSender::try_send` function.

defs.name: send
defs.docs: Attempts to send a value on this channel, returning it back if it could not be sent.

defs.name: send
defs.docs: Sends a value on this synchronous channel.

defs.name: try_send
defs.docs: Attempts to send a value on this channel without blocking.

defs.name: try_recv
defs.docs: Attempts to return a pending value on this receiver without blocking.

defs.name: timer
defs.docs: Timer optimized for I/O related operations

defs.name: Timer
defs.docs: A timer.

defs.name: Builder
defs.docs: Used to create a `Timer`.

defs.name: Timeout
defs.docs: A timeout, as returned by `Timer::set_timeout`.

defs.name: tick_duration
defs.docs: Set the tick duration.  Default is 100ms.

defs.name: num_slots
defs.docs: Set the number of slots.  Default is 256.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Set the capacity.  Default is 65536.

defs.name: build
defs.docs: Build a `Timer` with the parameters set on this `Builder`.

defs.name: set_timeout
defs.value: fn (&mut self, delay_from_now: Duration, state: T) -> Timeout
defs.docs: Set a timeout.

defs.name: cancel_timeout
defs.docs: Cancel a timeout.

defs.name: poll
defs.docs: Poll for an expired timer.
